@startuml context_map
skinparam backgroundColor transparent
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #ffffff
  BorderColor #1a5ad7
  FontColor #0b2147
  FontSize 14
}

rectangle "Order Fulfillment\nContext" as OF #lightblue
rectangle "Payment Processing\nContext" as PP
rectangle "Analytics Warehouse\nContext" as AW
rectangle "Pricing Engine\nContext" as PE

OF -down-> PP : **[U]** Order Fulfillment\n**[D]** Payment Processing\nPublished Language\n"Confirm Payment" API

AW -right-> OF : **[U]** Analytics Warehouse\n**[D]** Order Fulfillment\nCustomer-Supplier + Partnership\nPurpose-built order history view

PE -down-> OF : **[U]** Pricing Engine\n**[D]** Order Fulfillment\nCustomer-Supplier + ACL\nRate queries with translation

note right of PP
  **Published Language:**
  Well-defined REST API contract
  for confirming payment status
  before shipping
end note

note right of AW
  **Partnership:**
  Analytics team designs a
  purpose-built view for
  Order Fulfillment's needs

  Query via SQL
end note

note right of PE
  **Anti-Corruption Layer:**
  Pricing Engine provides
  shipping rate tables

  Order Fulfillment uses ACL to:
  - Query rates for standard shipping
  - Add calculated rates for express
    and international shipping
    not in rate tables

  Prevents coupling to external schema
end note

legend right
  **Integration Patterns:**
  Published Language: Well-defined API
  Partnership: Collaborative interface design
  ACL: Translation layer to isolate from external model

  **[U] = Upstream (Provider/Supplier)**
  **[D] = Downstream (Consumer/Customer)**
endlegend

@enduml
